  "prompt": "What I can do now because my 18 year will be completed in 17 January 2017. and most companies age limit is 18 year as on aug 2016?",
  "response": "Since your 18th birthday has already passed (on January 17, 2017), you are eligible to apply for jobs with companies that have an age limit of 18 years effective August 2016. Here are a few steps you can take:\n\n1. **Job Applications**: Start applying for jobs that interest you. Make sure to tailor your resume and cover letter to highlight your skills and experiences.\n\n2. **Internships**: Look for internships or apprenticeships that may help you gain valuable experience and potentially lead to full-time positions.\n\n3. **Networking**: Connect with people in your desired field through social media platforms like LinkedIn or attend industry events. Networking can open doors to job opportunities.\n\n4. **Skill Development**: While waiting for job opportunities, consider taking online courses or attending workshops to enhance your skills.\n\n5. **Volunteering**: Volunteering for organizations can provide you with experience and can be a great addition to your resume.\n\n6. **Freelancing**: If you have skills in writing, graphic design, programming, etc., consider freelancing. It can provide you with experience and income.\n\n7. **Prepare for Interviews**: Practice common interview questions and work on your communication skills to increase your chances of landing a job.\n\nBy taking these steps, you can improve your job prospects and find opportunities that align with your interests and career goals. Good luck!",
